==Ancient Greek==

===Pronunciation===
*συναγωγή / sunagōgē / soon-ag-o-gay'

===Etymology===
*From (the reduplicated form of) [[συνάγω]] {{GG|4863}}; an assemblage of persons; specifically a Jewish “synagogue” (the meeting or the place); by analogy a Christian church: 

===Noun===
'''συναγωγή'''

# [[assembly]], [[congregation]], [[synagogue]].

